[2] Leaf rust, berry disease - Kenya
Date: 24 Dec 2008
Source: Business Daily [edited]
<http://www.bdafrica.com/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=11969&Itemid=5844>


Kenya runs a weekly auction of the commodity at the Nairobi Coffee
Exchange (NCE) but has recently struggled to break even amid hitches
in production caused by among other things outbreaks of coffee berry
disease and coffee leaf rust.

At the peak of a production crisis that forced the NCE into an early
closure early this year [2008], several international dealers turned
their eyes on Ethiopia, effectively sounding a warning to rivals such
as Kenya.

[Byline: Allan Odhiambo]

